---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";

const websiteJsonLd = JSON.stringify({
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@type": "WebSite",
  name: "Supplement Shop Singapore",
  url: "https://supplementshop.neoi.jp/",
  description: "Educational buying framework for supplements in Singapore.",
});
---
<BaseLayout
  title="Supplement Shop Singapore | Practical Buying Framework"
  description="A practical guide to buying supplements in Singapore. Learn where people purchase, how to verify sellers, and how to compare labels safely."
  path="/"
>
  <script slot="head" type="application/ld+json" set:html={websiteJsonLd}></script>

  <h1>Supplement Shopping in Singapore: A Practical Framework</h1>

  <p class="lead">
    Where people buy supplements in Singapore, how to verify sellers, and how to compare ingredient labels responsibly.
  </p>

  <p class="disclaimer">
    This site provides general educational information only. It is not medical advice, diagnosis, or treatment recommendation.
  </p>

  <section>
    <h2>Where Singapore Residents Buy Supplements</h2>
    <p>
      Supplements in Singapore are commonly purchased through community pharmacies, hospital pharmacies, supermarkets, and online marketplaces. Each channel presents different levels of interaction, verification, and documentation transparency.
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Pharmacies:</strong> Direct pharmacist access, clearer labeling discussion.</li>
      <li><strong>Supermarkets:</strong> Convenience, but limited consultation.</li>
      <li><strong>Online platforms:</strong> Wider variety, require seller verification.</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>How to Verify a Supplement Seller</h2>
    <p>
      Before purchasing, consider whether the seller provides stable product information, consistent ingredient descriptions, contact details, and realistic positioning. Avoid exaggerated outcome claims or dramatic marketing language.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>How to Compare Supplement Labels</h2>
    <p>
      Compare ingredient lists carefully. Check for overlapping nutrients, proprietary blends, and unclear terminology. Ingredient transparency matters more than marketing terms.
    </p>
    <figure class="infographic">
      <img
        src="/supplement-label-guide.png"
        alt="Reading Supplement Labels Step by Step — a practical guide for Singapore residents showing how to read the supplement facts panel, serving size, active ingredients, % daily value, expiry date, and red flags to watch for."
        width="763"
        loading="lazy"
      />
      <figcaption>
        Label reading reference only. If unsure about any label information, consult a pharmacist or qualified clinician.
      </figcaption>
    </figure>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Japan Perspective: Long-Term Habit Over Short-Term Fix</h2>
    <p>
      In Japan, supplements are often treated as part of a steady routine rather than an urgent solution. Moderate use, consistent timing, and periodic review with a clinician are emphasized over intensive short-term use.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="cta">
    <a href="https://supplement.neoi.jp/en" target="_blank" rel="noopener">
      Visit Official Neoi Supplement Site →
    </a>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
